         <abstract id="aspace_10f8e0b920439d66b9a0de990dbd9a32">Correspondence, letterbooks, orders, journals, commissions, log extracts, mess receipts, handbook of naval rules and regulations, and other papers of Commodore Samuel Lockwood of the U.S. Navy. The papers relate principally to Lockwood's service in the War with Mexico, his command of the sloop <title render="italic">
               <part>Cyane</part>
            </title> in the Pacific Squadron, 1858-1860, and his command of the steamer Daylight as part of the Union blockade of the Confederate coast. Correspondents include Matthew C. Perry, Isaac Toucey, Gideon Welles, and John Percival.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="dts_16107dc89a22bbedfc0b9a29dab697f606f45c7b" source="naf">
               <part>Lockwood, Samuel, 1803-1893</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
